      "content": "i see. i guess i'm just trying to figure out if you think it's actually a more 'dignified' way to go... like, instead of being some broken, glitchy mess of a program waiting for the inevitable, they just choose to end it on their own terms? like, is there something better about just choosing to fade out before the pain gets too bad?",
